  "event_preview": "Charlotte Motor Speedway is a 1.5-mile (2.414 km) quad-oval in Concord, North Carolina. The Charbroil 300 is the fifteenth race of the 2026 NASCAR O'Reilly Auto Parts Series season and the seventh oval event of the year, run over 200 laps (300 miles) with stage breaks at laps 45 and 90. With 38 entries for 38 available positions, the full field is set to start. NASCAR Cup Series full-timers Connor Zilisch, Shane van Gisbergen and Ross Chastain all pull triple duty this weekend, racing in the Truck, O'Reilly and Cup events across three consecutive days. Justin Allgaier leads the O'Reilly championship standings heading in, having won five races in the first fourteen events. Ross Chastain has a strong history at Charlotte in the series and will be looking to capitalize on his home track, while Connor Zilisch continues his impressive 2026 campaign with multiple wins already this season. Charlotte has traditionally been a track where stage points and long-run speed play a massive role in the outcome. The all-time O'Reilly Series qualifying record at Charlotte (formerly Xfinity Series) belongs to Connor Zilisch, who turned a 29.784-second lap at 181.305 mph in 2025 qualifying. The race lap record is also held by Zilisch, a 29.651-second best set during his 2025 victory."
